1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,840
 So welcome back.

2
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:04,560
 Now we're gonna talk about how you use CSS within HTML.

3
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:08,880
 How you take these CSS rules and apply them to the various parts of HTML.

4
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:10,800
 And there are three basic ways that we do this.

5
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,400
 One is we take an HTML tag and use the style attribute and

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:20,600
 just put those little CSS key value, you know, CSS settings right there, very close.

7
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:23,160
 The other thing is you can put it in the background of the HTML document,

8
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:24,880
 usually in the head area.

9
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:28,640
 And the other, probably most common thing, especially when the styles get large,

10
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:31,720
 is an external style sheet that's a separately loaded file with a separate

11
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:32,840
 request response cycle.

12
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:39,640
 So we'll start with sort of the simplest but sort of least used of these things.

13
00:00:39,640 --> 00:00:43,800
 And that is, like I said, you can put a style attribute on any tag.

14
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:47,720
 And you say, any attribute, you know, you say, it's got a double quote and

15
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,720
 a bunch of stuff and another double quote.

16
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:54,000
 And in there is a series of CSS rules that are basically CSS setting,

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,680
 like border style colon and then the border style setting that you want.

18
00:00:57,680 --> 00:01:00,680
 And so in here I'm saying I would like a solid border, I would like it red and

19
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:02,280
 I'd like it to be five pixels.

20
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:09,040
 And that effectively determines how that particular thing gets painted, right?

21
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:12,760
 In this particular one I said font family monospace for that particular paragraph.

22
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:16,360
 So this paragraph is painted with a font family monospace.

23
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:18,280
 And so you can just put these things here.

24
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:21,560
 I put on the body tag, I want an Arial Sans Serif font.

25
00:01:21,560 --> 00:01:24,800
 So the whole body is not Times New Roman,

26
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:27,880
 except for the fact that this particular one is monospace.

27
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:33,920
 And so these two tags are rendering opinions about what the font's supposed to be.

28
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:37,720
 But because this one is closer, the monospace wins here, but

29
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:42,400
 the Arial wins everywhere else because none of these other tags render an opinion.

30
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:47,080
 And so that's kind of the cascading bit, meaning the closer it is,

31
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:52,120
 the more priority that it has, unless of course they put important up here.

32
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,640
 And important is something we'll talk about later.

